We will still offer a robust free, ad-supported option with access to all of our core features.\",\"question\":\"Why is Weather Underground's Ad Free experience becoming a paid subscription?\"},{\"answer\":\"Users who don't operate an active Personal Weather Station and who are currently accessing an Ad Free experience at no cost will be moved to a free, ad-supported experience on March 5, 2024.\",\"question\":\"I've been accessing Ad Free at no cost. When am I no longer eligible to do so?\"},{\"answer\":\"No. Weather Underground subscriptions are only valid on Weather Underground. A subscription with The Weather Channel is only valid on weather.com and The Weather Channel apps. While the same email address and password work across your account on both The Weather Channel and Weather Underground, subscriptions only work with the brand for which they were purchased.\",\"question\":\"If I purchase an Ad Free subscription on Weather Underground, can I also use it to get an Ad Free experience on weather.com or The Weather Channel apps for iOS or Android?\"},{\"answer\":\" We're sorry for the inconvenience but at this time, due to tax regulations, subscriptions are limited to users located in the United States. We are currently working on making international subscriptions available. You can still sign up for a free account and become a member of our Weather Underground community if you're located outside the United States.\",\"question\":\"I'm based outside the United States. A Premium subscription for the WU iOS or Android app offers additional features beyond no ads, including Smart Forecasts for planning outdoor activities and Extended Hourly Forecasts up to 15 days in the future.\",\"question\":\"Can I use my wunderground.com Ad Free subscription on the WU app for iOS or Android?\"},{\"answer\":\"No. As of right now, your Ad Free subscription will not allow you to get Premium access on either the WU iOS or Android app (and vice versa). To make sure we keep providing the most accurate and valuable weather data to our users, we've updated our policy. Ad Free now depends on your Personal Weather Station remaining active. This means the Personal Weather Station has sent us data within the last 30 days. If you have a Personal Weather Station but it's been inactive for 30 days or more, you'll see ads on wunderground.com.\",\"question\":\"Why am I seeing ads, even though I have a Personal Weather Station?\"},{\"answer\":\"You have two options to regain an access to the Ad Free experience:
Bring your Personal Weather Station back online - We understand technical issues can sometimes arise. Our support resources can help you troubleshoot common problems and get your Personal Weather Station sending us data again, at which point you'll automatically regain access to Ad Free.
Upgrade to a paid subscription - If you\u2019re not planning to send PWS data to us but would still like to enjoy an Ad Free experience, we offer both a monthly and an annual Ad Free subscription plan that zaps the ads and offers additional benefits like extended forecasts and exclusive features.\",\"question\":\"How can I go back to not seeing ads?\"},{\"answer\":\"When your Personal Weather Station starts sending data to Weather Underground again, your access to Ad Free will be reinstated, but you need to log out of wunderground.com and log back in to start seeing the website without ads.\u00A0\",\"question\":\"If I bring my Personal Weather Station back online, will my access to Ad Free return automatically?\"},{\"answer\":\" If your Personal Weather Station was registered with us prior to August 2023 and has uploaded data to our network in the last 30 days, Ad Free is available to you at no charge in exchange for the data you contribute.
